article.headline: Northeastern 69, Binghamton 57
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) -- Sophomore Jose Barea scored 24 points and Marcus Barrens added 16 to lead Northeastern over Binghamton 69-57 Wednesday night in an America East Conference basketball game. After trailing 34-31 at halftime, Northeastern (17-9, 11-4) took the lead for good with 17:13 to play on a 3-pointer by Barea, making the score 40-39. The Huskies used a 12-2 run with 6:38 left to put the game away. Gavotte Wilson and Bennett Davis scored nine points apiece for Northeastern, which won it's sixth game in it's last seven. Troy Haley had 13 points for the Bracts (12-14, 8-7), who shot just 28 percent and turned the ball over 14 times in the final period. Brandon Carter scored 10 points and Joel Cases added nine. Billy William's had 11 rebounds and eight assists.
